Add a custom DistroLauncher. This will allow packaging NixOS-WSL as an appx package and upload it to the MS Store eventually

This is a custom reimplementation of DistroLauncher in C# (instead of C++, which is what the reference implementation uses)
The rewrite gives us greater flexibility in extending the DistroLauncher with additional features, e.g. upgrading to newer releases of NixOS-WSL with something like nixos update

  • Fix WslLaunchInteractive return codes
  • Updating works
  • systemd implementation in version output
  • Update.cs: Use mktemp instead of a hard-coded directory
  • Check for nixos-unstable channel before overwriting it
  • Make secrets more easily accessible by using something like age or sops
  • Put a decryption key into the repo secrets

Future ideas

  • Rescue Shell
  • Rollback
  • Updating to specific git revisions instead of the bundled tarball's version

Related: #63 #78

Description of changes

pre-commit-hook-ensure-sops is a Python package, as the name implies, for
testing sops-using repositories for
leaking secrets i.e., committing unencrypted secrets that should be
(automatically) encrypted by sops. It is primarily implemented for use as a
pre-commit hook but the command-line entrypoint is generally usable for
checking sops files for unencrypted secrets or invalid structure.

After addition to nixpkgs it can be more cleanly used by e.g.,
pre-commit-hooks.nix
(cachix/pre-commit-hooks.nix#212).
